  "event_preview": "Kansas Speedway is a 1.5-mile (2.4 km) tri-oval in Kansas City, Kansas, opened in 2001 and repaved and reconfigured in 2012 to introduce the variable banking that defines the current layout — 17 to 20 degrees in the turns, tapering to 9 to 11 degrees on the frontstretch and 5 degrees on the backstretch. The multi-groove surface rewards both high-lane runners and drivers who can work the bottom, and the track's combination of long straightaways and sweeping turns places a premium on aerodynamic balance and late-race tyre life. The Kansas Lottery 300 is the ninth race of the 2026 NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series season and the first of two Kansas dates on the calendar. Severe weather forced the cancellation of all Friday on-track activity, meaning the starting lineup was set by the rule book rather than qualifying, placing Carson Kvapil on pole at the front of the 37-car field. It is also the second of four Dash 4 Cash races, with Brent Crews, Justin Allgaier, Carson Kvapil and Sheldon Creed eligible for the $100,000 bonus after being the highest-finishing O'Reilly Series regulars at Bristol. The all-time qualifying lap record at Kansas belongs to Matt Kenseth, who turned a 29.204-second lap (184.906 mph) in October 2015.",
